        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 5:30PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 530 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
George Payne State Park, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Oxford, Water Valley, Holly Springs National Forest, George Payne
State Park, Pope, Springdale, Burgess, Courtland, Taylor, College
Hill, Shuford, and Eureka Springs.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
